HEADWORD: Margent
<hw>Mar"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. See
<er>Margin</er>.]</ety> <def>A margin; border; brink; edge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The beached <qex>margent</qex> of the sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Margent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Margent
<hw>Mar"gent</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To enter or note down upon the
margin of a page; to margin.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Mir. for
Mag.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Margin</ent>⟦br⟧
